title: Requirements: support devices without root
message:
Requirements: support devices without root

  * non rooted devices probably do not have busybox and there is not way to
    install it manually.
    also we do not use busybox for non root features, means we can launch the
    app without busybox in non root mode.

  * rooted devices have some features, which require busybox. show a warning
    on rooted devices without busybox, but let them launch the app anyways.

  * adapt strings and warning messages

title: Styles: use translucent theme
message:
Styles: use translucent theme

   we are setting the theme dynamically at runtime.

   previously we set the AppTheme.Light in manifest by default, which
   will always show the light theme, then load the app, set the theme
   and render the content.

   this resulted in the light theme appearing before setting the dark theme,
   which is pretty ugly.

Reference: https://plus.google.com/+VasilisK/posts/f8wXh1tyTZc

Environment
  * ambient temperature (°C / °F)

  * pressure (hPa / mbar)
  * relative humidity (%)

Motion
  * accelerometer (including gravity)
  * accelerometer linear (excluding gravity)
  * gravity
  * gyroscope
  * gyroscope uncalibrated (jelly bean mr2+)
  * rotation vector
  * step counter (kitkat and above)

Position
  * game rotation vector
  * geomagnetic rotation vector
  * magnetic field sensor (µT)
  * magnetic field sensor uncalibrated (µT, jelly bean mr2+)
  * proximity

title: GpuUtils: fixup opengl calls for lollipop
message:
GpuUtils: fixup opengl calls for lollipop

Pre lollipop always had an OpenGL ES context running somewhere
in the framework.

However this is not the case with lollipop and we fail to get
information about OpenGL ES because of the missing context.

To fix this issue we could use a surfaceview, which is useless because we
will not render.
So let's go a bit hardcore and make use of low level opengl calls to create
our context, get the information and destroy the context.

i am not an expert, this code may eat your dog, but it seems to work for me

title: introduce flasher and file picker
message:
introduce flasher and file picker

introduces a custom file picker, which can highlight matching files
for the flasher we want to only flash zip files, so the target extension
is set to zip and the file picker highlights all zip files.

the file picker is fully using root, so we can pick
ANY file at ANY directory and use it.

this allows us to flash zip files from /data, /system or any other path,
as well as any external storage we have.

the flasher allows to specify multiple files and flashes them one after
another. the flasher honors the order the user added the files.
this allows to flash for example GAPPS first, then a package which modifies
the previously flashed GAPPS and then a third packages, which removes them
again (pretty useless task but it would be possible)

also the flasher allows to specify the type of recovery you have.
by default it creates a script for CWM and OpenRecovery, but allows to
only create the script for CWM or OpenRecovery as well.

title: DC: add CPU Control
message:
DC: add CPU Control

allows you to change the following:
  *) Max frequency on all cores
  *) Min frequency on all cores
  *) Governor on all cores
  *) internal I/O scheduler

its fully multicore aware :)

it also displays the current frequency, max frequency and governor for
all cores, together with an option to change to auto refresh rate of
the status or just turn it off completly as well as hiding the status.

these preferences get saved and autorestore the next time you open it.

as well includes a bootup receiver to restore changes on bootup.

title: performance: add power scheduler option
message:
performance: add power scheduler option

the power scheduler allows the cpu to group tasks on a core, until it
reaches its maximum load and switches on the next core.

this is an attempt to save battery, as it uses the whole capacity of the
cores, until it turns on the next core.
but this also sacrifices power.

0 for disabled, 1 for balanced, 2 for aggressive.

this is useful as on different phones there may are different locations for
files which have the same function, eg torch.

this allows to pass in an array to the method, it checks the paths and if
a file exists, the path of it is getting returned.
